This paper proposes a novel framework for 3D vehicle detection and tracking from monocular videos, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as object detection and instance association. The framework also utilizes trajectory prediction and motion learning, which are related to robotics (RO) and machine learning (LG) respectively. The paper focuses on improving the accuracy of 3D tracking, which is a common goal in artificial intelligence (AI) research. Finally, the experiments are conducted on datasets related to autonomous driving, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (CR). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CR.
